        "text_tegpMJ": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Cotes Mill is unlike any flooring showroom you could imagine. It has become a destination that people travel to from across the country. It is also very popular with American fans of deVOL’s TV series ‘For The Love of Kitchens’ which Floors of Stone’s director co-hosts with his partner, renowned interior designer, Helen Parker.<br/><br/>Floors of Stone has been selling high-quality flooring since 2007, when we started supplying affordable natural stone tiles to our sister company, deVOL Kitchens. We are now a leading supplier of limestone, marble, sandstone, slate, travertine, porcelain, terracotta and reclaimed encaustic tiles, along with our own range of wood flooring.<br/><br/>In 2013, we moved our showroom to the historic Cotes Mill in Leicestershire. The whole building has a wonderful sense of atmosphere and character. Floors of Stone’s showroom occupies the main entrance ground floor and galleried mezzanine. There are dozens of large format displays of our most popular flooring as well as individual tiles of every product we sell. There are four further floors of kitchen displays, gifts and antiques, as well as twelve acres of stunning grounds, including a secret garden and a peacock pen.</p>",
